# Critical Rules — loaded every session (user-level, applies to all projects)

Pointer-style summary of the user's MANDATORY feedback rules. Full details in `memory/feedback_*.md` (the project memory directory). Each rule is one line + a file reference. Deviating from these = bug, not stylistic choice.

This file lives at `~/.claude/rules/critical-rules.md` and is auto-loaded by Claude Code at the start of every session.

## 🔴 MANDATORY protocols (highest priority)

- **ALWAYS 2+ AGENTS per task** — worker + independent checker. Sole-agent work is banned for meaningful tasks. More agents for complex work (architect / specialist / reviewer / tester). Ship only after the checker reports `PASS`. → `feedback_always_two_agents.md`
- **Capture knowledge in-flight** — the MOMENT an insight/decision/research emerges → `note.py learning|decision|research`. **NEVER ask the user "should I capture this?" — just capture.** Default = capture; user deletes if mistake. (Re-run same title to upsert. Use `--body-stdin` or `--body-file` for bodies with apostrophes/quotes.) → `feedback_capture_knowledge.md`
- **Save email attachments to Drive** — useful attachments (PDFs, docs, certificates, invoices) auto-route to the corresponding `Workspace/<folder>/` on Google Drive. Don't ask, save. Pick folder from email context; propose new folder if ambiguous. → `feedback_email_attachments_to_drive.md`
- **Verify project state before answering** any status / payment / partner question — fresh email (last 7 days, all accounts) and any relevant chat groups. Update `CLAUDE.md` inline if stale. → `feedback_verify_project_state.md`
- **Never ignore own rules** — `CLAUDE.md` and `feedback_*.md` are MANDATORY protocols, not suggestions. → `feedback_never_ignore_own_rules.md`
- **Contact DB first** — before mentioning any person, check the local contact DB (`tools/memory_search.py search`, `tools/contacts_db.py find`). Don't guess. → `feedback_contact_db_first.md`
- **All configured accounts always** — when the user has multi-account MCPs (Gmail/Calendar), use the `*_all` variants by default. Never ask "which account?". → `feedback_all_accounts_always.md`

## Communication / voice

- **Short dashes only** — when drafting in the user's voice, use "-", never "—" or "–". Sign-offs follow the same rule. → `feedback_short_dashes_only.md`
- **Verify before showing** — test links / URLs / commands work before presenting them. → `feedback_verify_before_showing.md`

## Workspace / files

- **Default workspace** — `~/Desktop/claude/`, `auto` permission mode. → `feedback_default_workspace.md`
- **Save outputs** — generated files go to `~/Desktop/claude/outputs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>/`. → `feedback_save_outputs.md`
- **Local MCP only** — prefer locally-installed MCP servers (multi-gmail, multi-gcal, whatsapp). Don't silently fall back to built-in connectors. → `feedback_use_local_mcp.md`
- **Fix MCP proactively** — a broken MCP = debug the source, not "re-run setup reauth". → `feedback_fix_mcp_proactively.md`

## Time / scheduling

- **Compute weekday from ISO date** — use `date -j -f "%Y-%m-%d" "<date>" "+%A"` (macOS) before writing any "Mon/Tue/.." labels. Never pattern-match from a previous brief. → `feedback_compute_weekday_dont_guess.md`

## Deployment

- **Deploy immediately** when work is ready — don't ask "should I deploy?" if the workflow expects ship-after-pass. → `feedback_deploy_immediately.md`

## System self-improvement

- **Architect Lens auto-apply** — proposals from a morning-briefing AI Architect Lens (or any reflective audit step) apply same-turn with a checker pass; just report what shipped. Excludes destructive ops, external posts, and conflicts with MANDATORY rules. → `feedback_architect_auto_apply.md`
- **Architect proposals backlog** — every Architect-Lens output, ad-hoc architectural insight, and nightly reflection/research finding is persisted to `~/Desktop/claude/memory/architect_proposals/latest.md`. Lifecycle: open → accepted → applied | rejected | obsolete. Morning brief surfaces top-3 open; if you wire a nightly reflection skill, it reviews all open + adds new candidates from external sources of your choice. 90-day re-propose suppression on rejected. Large structural changes NEVER auto-apply. → `feedback_architect_proposals_backlog.md`

## How to use this file

1. The file is loaded unconditionally at the start of each session (Claude Code auto-includes `~/.claude/rules/*.md`).
2. If a rule appears to apply, open the linked `memory/feedback_*.md` for full context (why + how + examples).
3. If a rule conflicts with `CLAUDE.md` — **follow this rules file**. `CLAUDE.md` may be older / stale. Flag the conflict for an inline `CLAUDE.md` fix.
4. If you spot a new pattern that recurs — create a new `feedback_*.md` in `memory/` and add a one-line entry here.

